result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Cory M. Wilson was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cory M. Wilson in court with attorney Walter Arthur Piel.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 1 in 14CF81.  State will move to dismiss Ct 2 in 14CF81 along with charges in 14TR1642 and 14TR1643.  Atty Piel agrees.  Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 1 in 14CF81.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court questions Atty Piel.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 1 in 14CF81.  Court will dismiss Ct 2 in 14CF81 along with charges in 14TR1642 & 14TR1643.
Parties are not requesting a PSI.  Counsel make sentencing statements.  Defendant makes statement to the Court.
BY THE COURT:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 36 months with the following conditions:  *Serve 6 months in the Marquette County Jail.  Sentence to commence forthwith.  Granted huber.  (Court will not object to huber for seeking work)  Granted good-time credit.  *Pay fine and costs of $1,694.00.  *35 month DL revocation.  *35 month ignition interlock.  *AODA and comply with any conditions.  *Maintain absolute sobriety.  *Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $250.00.  *Bond on file to be applied and any balance returned.
